TUNISIA head coach Mondher Kebaier was sacked on Sunday, the day after his side's Africa Cup of Nations quarterfinal exit to Burkina Faso. Kebaier, 51, who had been in charge since August 2019, will be replaced by his 50-year-old deputy coach Jalel Kadri, the Tunisia Football Federation confirmed. Tunisia, the 2004 African Cup of Nations champions, lost 1-0 to 10-man Burkina Faso on Saturday in Cameroon. - AFP 